                <p>
                    Ben Carter is a board-certified Psychiatric-Mental Health Nurse Practitioner (PMHNP-BC) who brings a warm, person-centered approach to care. He received his Master of Science in Nursing from Yale University and has extensive experience working with adults dealing with anxiety, ADHD, and life transitions.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Ben is a firm believer in the power of listening. He works diligently to understand each patient's unique story and goals. His practice combines careful medication management with practical, skills-based therapeutic techniques to empower patients on their wellness journey. He is passionate about reducing stigma and making mental healthcare accessible and approachable for everyone.
